<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-12T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-12T14:00:00-05:00" n="974" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d974">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.24/72: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-12T20:00:00+01:00">November
                                    12, 1943—8 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 8:07 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>7894. For Alling from Hoskins. General Crain cabling War Department today
                            that British War Office advise they have not as yet made any deliveries
                            of military equipment to Saudi Arabia and have agreed not to make any
                            deliveries pending further discussions and agreement with us. Their main
                            concern remains that no excessive quantities be furnished.
                            [Hoskins.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>